  "riddle": "1. Unearth the small town cradled by the banks of the Appomattox River—what are its geographical coordinates?\n\n2. What altitude does this quaint locality rise to, in meters above the sea?\n\n3. Traverse the realm of education and discover how many universities flourish in the vicinity of that town.\n\n4. Now, combine the elevation you found in clue 2 with the number of universities from clue 3 to find a new total.\n\n5. In a year marked by conflict, a significant battle unfolded just nearby—can you unveil the date when the fight commenced?\n\n6. Seek the politician, a stalwart of his party from 1866 until 1886, who championed the cause of the post-war populace. What political affiliation did he represent?\n\n7. With political ironies abound, calculate the number of days that have passed between June 17, 1863, and March 15, 2026.\n\n8. Delve into the binary realm: what lies at the heart of your seventh answer when you count the number of 1-bits in its representation?\n\n9. The final task beckons: compute the absolute difference between the elevation from clue 2 and the number of universities from clue 3, then take that result modulo 10.",
